posts.name: Jackson Elia
posts.cooked:
Hello,

My team is using TrajectoryGenerator.generateTrajectory() and SwerveControllerCommand to follow trajectories. It works fine normally, but when I added a middle waypoint it crashed. What would cause this to happen (the middle waypoint is a Translation2d object that is being given 2 doubles for x and y position.

What would cause a middle waypoint to make generateTrajectory crash?

posts.name: Tipy
posts.cooked:

posts.name: Jackson Elia
posts.cooked: This isn’t pathplanner, it’s WPILib’s built in class.

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked: We need more information.  What are the values of the parameters?  What is the message / stack trace when it crashes?

posts.name: Sam Mulvey
posts.cooked: Normally it asks for a List.of() translation2ds. Even if it’s only one it takes In a list

posts.name: Sam Mulvey
posts.cooked: Oh also if the spline is not able to be generated because it deems the bend to be too tight then you will get a printout like “spline not able to be parameterized” or something similar

posts.name: Jackson Elia
posts.cooked:
Where is the stack trace? The only error I could see said that the generateTrajectory() method was causing the crash.

The path was making it go from 0, 0 and 0 rotation to 2, 0, and 0 rotation. The waypoint was at 1.9, 0. One thing to note was that the actual rotation of the robot was 180. I don’t know why this would cause the trajectory to error out though.

posts.name: Gavin Matthews
posts.cooked: It really would help us help you to see more of the error message and more of your code.
